  "playingCareerSummary": "Former New Zealand captain (1997-2006) and one of the most respected tactical minds of his generation: 111 Tests, 280 ODIs for NZ. Played for Chennai Super Kings in the inaugural 2008 IPL season before retiring and taking over as head coach in 2009.",
  "bio": "The most successful head coach in IPL history by titles won (5). Took charge of Chennai Super Kings in 2009 and has led them through every season of the franchise's existence barring 2016 and 2017, when CSK was suspended — during that period he coached Rising Pune Supergiant, taking them to the 2017 final (lost to MI by 1 run). Has guided CSK to five IPL titles (2010, 2011, 2018, 2021, 2023). Known for a calm, methodical tactical style and a remarkable partnership with captain MS Dhoni.",
